## Appendix C — Web UI: Cockpit module vs. clustr React SPA

A side-by-side review of what each product surfaces in the browser. Source
material on the clustervisor side is the `cockpit-clustervisor-1.25.04-4844.noarch`
RPM (a single-bundle webpack app: `index.js` 6.0 MB unpacked, `index.css`,
three HTML entry pages — `main.html`, `clustervisor.html`, `console.html` —
mounted at `/usr/share/cockpit/clustervisor/`). Page/feature labels were
extracted from the compiled JS bundle's string table; about 1,800 unique
strings of length ≥ 5 starting with a capital letter give a reliable map of
the UI surface. clustr side: `web/src/routes/` (11 routes) +
`web/src/components/` (8 top-level components) + the shadcn `ui/` primitive
layer. Bundle is built by Vite + React 19 + TanStack Query + Tailwind v4,
embedded into the Go binary via `embed.FS`.

### Architecture comparison

| Aspect | clustervisor (Cockpit) | clustr (React SPA) | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Embedding model** | Cockpit module — runs *inside* a host's Cockpit (`https://host:9090/clustervisor/`). Inherits Cockpit's host-level menu (System, Networking, Storage, Services, Accounts, Terminal). | Standalone SPA served by `clustr-serverd` at `/`. No host-level chrome. | clustervisor gets host operations free via Cockpit; clustr is fully self-contained. |
| **Auth** | Cockpit's PAM-backed login (`/login`). Sessions are Cockpit's, not the app's. The "Limit Access" / "Switch to limited access" controls let admins drop privilege within a session. | Cookie session (HMAC) + bearer API tokens. Bootstrap admin (`clustr/clustr`) with forced password change on first login. Roles: admin / director / pi / viewer. | Different threat models — clustervisor inherits OS PAM; clustr owns its own users/roles end-to-end. |
| **Bundle stack** | webpack (PatternFly 4, ApexCharts 3.41, noVNC, Monaco editor, focus-trap, DOMPurify, FileSaver, react, QUnit). Bundle ships compiled with .gz next to .js. | Vite + React 19 + TanStack Query + Tailwind v4 + shadcn (Radix) + Lucide + Sonner. No charts library, no editor, no console viewer. | clustervisor's bundle is ~6× larger and ships heavy components (noVNC, Monaco, Apex) for browser-resident workflows. |
| **HTML entry pages** | 3 (`main.html`, `clustervisor.html`, `console.html`) — separate page contexts for the dashboard shell, the redirect bridge, and the embedded console viewer. | 1 (Vite-emitted `index.html`). | clustervisor splits the console viewer into its own page so noVNC/SPICE/RDP can be opened in a popup; clustr has no console viewer. |
| **Update model** | RPM upgrade replaces `/usr/share/cockpit/clustervisor/`; user reloads. | RPM upgrade replaces the binary; UI is in the binary; user reloads. | Same outcome; clustr is one-step. |
| **Translatability** | Cockpit's `po.js` system, `<title translatable>`. | None visible; UI strings are inline in TSX. | clustr is English-only today. |
| **Routes** | All within the Cockpit module's mount point (`/clustervisor/...`); navigation is internal. | React Router routes (`/login`, `/setup`, `/set-password`, `/nodes`, `/images`, `/identity`, `/groups`, `/slurm`, `/settings`, `/activity`, `/stub`). | clustr has 10 functional routes; clustervisor exposes ~20+ functional pages from the bundle (Dashboard, Cluster Configuration, ClusterVisor Config, ClusterVisor UI Configuration, ClusterVisor Software Upgrade, LDAP Settings, Email Settings, LogVisor Settings, Scheduler Settings, SSH Settings, Synced File Settings, Cloner Settings, Distros, Stateless image, Netboot, Authorized public keys, File Manager, Code Editor, Terminal, Power, Sensors, Event Log, Remote Desktop, Serial Console, Rack Layout, Plugins, Monitoring Alerts). |

