## Appendix D — Cloning, imaging, and initramfs internals

A side-by-side review of how each product turns "blank machine" into
"running OS." Source on the clustervisor side: `/usr/lib/clustervisor/cloner/*.pm`
(8,216 lines of Perl across 9 files), `/usr/lib/clustervisor/server/cv_serverd/{cloner,ipxe_server}.py`
(1,645 lines of Python), `/usr/lib/clustervisor/client/initrd/*.py` (470 lines),
`/usr/libexec/clustervisor/cloner_initrd/` (Buildroot 2019.02 tree with
116 enabled packages, busybox + dropbear + munge + intel-syscfg overlay).
Source on clustr side: `internal/image/factory.go` (2,267 lines),
`internal/image/{layout,isoinstaller}/` (~3,400 lines), `internal/deploy/*.go`
(rsync, raid, zfs, finalize, network, efiboot — ~5,000 lines total),
`internal/initramfs/kernel.go`, `internal/pxe/{boot,dhcp,tftp,pxe}.go`,
`internal/server/handlers/boot.go` (PXE routing), `scripts/build-initramfs.sh`
(1,300+ lines of bash), `scripts/initramfs-init.sh` (PID 1 init template).

